The Bipartisan Safer Communities Act has successfully denied over 500 illegal gun purchases by people under 21 years old who posed a danger to communities. This legislation aims to keep guns out of the hands of young people with criminal records or deemed a danger to themselves or others. It is part of a broader plan to reduce crime and improve public safety. The article highlights the drop in crime in 2023, including a significant decrease in homicides. The president has taken executive action to combat gun violence and calls on Congress to enact universal background checks, ban assault weapons, end immunity for the gun industry, and pass a national red flag law. The goal is to prevent suicides, domestic violence, and mass shootings.